ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  adding a million =
users a day</a> as people flocked to Reddit to discuss their plans to trade=
 GameStop Corp. and other meme stocks. Imagine if Reddit put a button next =
to each GameStop post saying =E2=80=9Cbuy GME,=E2=80=9D and if you clicked =
the button you could buy shares directly through Reddit? (I guess maybe add=
 another button like =E2=80=9CYOLO GME options=E2=80=9D so you could buy th=
e call options too?) That just seems like it would be good business, and go=
od customer service, each in a loose approximate way. Probably some complia=
nce issues with that button. Probably some customers would be sad if they b=
ought GameStop for $400 with one click after reading an enthusiastic but in=
accurate Reddit post. Probably some lawsuits. Still the basic business idea=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cthe place where people go to enthusiastically disc=
uss stocks should also let them buy those stocks directly=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0has an appeal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/31156532.260450/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMy8wNC8xMy90d2l0=
