er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  he once said, on television</a>, and that=
=E2=80=99s one of the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/31156532.260450/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9lbG9ubXVzay9zdGF0dXMvMTI3ODc=
2NDczNjg3Njc3MzM4Mw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd3c41d55" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> nicer thing=
s</a> he has said about the US Securities and Exchange Commission. If Elon =
Musk tells Twitter=E2=80=99s engineers =E2=80=9Cput a button on the site th=
at lets people buy stock in companies that I tweet about, or in companies t=
hat have names that are similar to words that I tweet,=E2=80=9D and a lawye=
r pipes up to say =E2=80=9Cthe SEC might have some concerns about that,=E2=
=80=9D he will scream expletives and tell them to make the button bigger. T=
his is not how the leaders of most retail stock brokerages think about thei=
r relationship with the SEC, and it gives Musk certain, uh, competitive adv=
antages.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The SEC has been burned b=
efore and seems to be afraid to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/31156532.260450/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
